Eliminations:
@BillyStevens999 & @GypsyPranay won the most elims on The Duel (3 wins), @connorreda won the most elims on Free Agents (3 wins), and @HeyyyJj from Cutthroat has the best single season elim record (4 wins). Interestingly he did so on the season with the fewest elims.

Nr. 1!
Daddy’s Home - St. Vincent
I love St. Vincent and this might just be her best album yet. The production is next level, fantastic songwriting and some of her greatest vocal performances. An all-time great album. 
Fav songs: Down, Down And Out Downtown, Somebody Like Me https://t.co/b5kcfJqUds

Nr. 2!
Collapsed In Sunbeams - Arlo Parks
This album is pretty much perfect. Arlo is the next big thing and I cannot wait to see where she goes from here. And this is her debut!! Insane talent, voice, songwriting, just an absolute star ❤️💫
Fav songs: Eugene, Hope, Green Eyes https://t.co/nv7tcQZC3X

Nr. 3!
A Beginner’s Mind - Sufjan Stevens & Angelo De Augustine
Absolutely stunning album ❤️ I'm a huge Sufjan fan, his  and Angelo's voice meld together in perfect harmony to make this beautiful record.
Fav songs: Murder and Crime, Reach Out, Fictional California https://t.co/bw0VwOA4D4

Nr. 4!
HLDYTIGL - Big Red Machine
This album is like cocaine for indie heads. It's just a bunch of great indie artists, with Bon Iver's Justin Vernon and The National's Aaron Dessner at the forefront, having a blast making music. Love it ❤️
Fav songs: Hutch, Latter Days, Renegade https://t.co/pVpEyyWvSD

Nr. 5!
Sling - Clairo
I took way too long to give this album a listen but holy shit has it had a hold on me since. Clairo's voice and the absolutely beautiful instrumentation make this album feel like the nicest hug. 
Fav songs: Zinnias, Blouse, Amoeba https://t.co/91cGMNbEIg

Nr. 6!
Home Video - Lucy Dacus
This album contains some of the best songwriting of the year. Lucy delivers a low key but beautiful vocal performance throughout and I enjoyed every moment.
Fav songs: Hot & Heavy, VBS, Thumbs https://t.co/4TbHAaPX1L

Nr. 7!
Good Woman - The Staves
The queens of harmonizing are back with probably their best work yet. Super solid collection of beautiful songs. Been a fan of them for a while and this album did not disappoint. 
Fav songs: Good Woman, Next Year Next Time, Nothing's Gonna Happen. https://t.co/FxnjrmZDSF

Nr. 8!
Jubilee - Japanese Breakfast
This album is just so great, the vibes are emaculate, everyone should do themselves a favor and give this record a listen. It would be much higher but I felt it lacked a bit of consistency.
Fav songs: Be Sweet, Posing in Bondage, Slide Tackle https://t.co/PAtzeVmHoC

Nr. 9!
I Know I'm Funny haha - Faye Webster
I just love the sound of this album and Faye's voice. The instrumentation complements her perfectly and you get this great album front to back.
Fav songs: Sometimes, Cheers, Half of Me https://t.co/nRbIPriefC

Nr. 10!
Happier Than Ever - Billie Eilish
I didn't think I would like this album based off of the singles but I loved the finished product! Great production and songs that have stuck with me.
